Key Match Events: Mike Yastrzemski hit a game-winning home run in the seventh inning to lead the San Francisco Giants to a 5-4 victory over the Milwaukee Brewers.
Lamonte Wade Jr. grounded out to second, scoring Grant McCray to open the game with a 1-0 lead for the Giants.
Matt Chapman hit a solo home run in the top of the fourth inning.
Grant McCray added a solo home run in the top of the fifth inning.
Post-Match Reflections: Following the win, San Francisco moved to 67-66 on the season, keeping themselves alive in the chase to get back into a National League Wild Card spot.
